metatags.og:site_name: U.S. Department of Homeland Security Transportation Security Administration
metatags.og:title: Participating States and Eligible Digital IDs | Transportation Security Administration
metatags.og:description: The TSA's digital ID program allows travelers from participating states to use mobile driver's licenses or state IDs at select TSA checkpoints. These digital IDs can be added to platforms like Apple Wallet, Google Wallet, or state-specific apps. The program aims to enhance security and streamline the identity verification process. However, travelers must still carry a physical ID as a backup. You can find more details on the TSA's official page.

metatags.twitter:title: Mobile ID Terms and Conditions
metatags.og:title: Mobile ID Terms and Conditions
metatags.og:description: These Terms and Conditions apply when you, an applicant, add a Driver's License or Identification Card ("Credential") issued by the Virginia Department of Motor Vehicles ("DMV") to an application ("Digital Wallet") that will allow you to present the digital or mobile form of your Credential ("Mobile ID") to verify your identity, demographics, and driving privileges with merchants, government entities, law enforcement, and other requesters instead of presenting your physical state-issued credential according to Virginia law. DMV reserves the right to update these Terms at any time and without notice as permitted by law, and your continued use of this mobile ID constitutes agreement to all such changes. You may elect to add a digital or electronic version of your physical Credential to the Digital Wallet.
metatags.twitter:creator: @VirginiaDMV

metatags.og:site_name: U.S. Department of Homeland Security Transportation Security Administration
metatags.og:title: TSA expands acceptance of digital IDs to West Virginia | Transportation Security Administration
metatags.og:description: CHARLESTON, W.Va. –The Transportation Security Administration (TSA) is now accepting West Virginia-issued mobile driver licenses (mDLs) at checkpoints with digital ID readers nationwide.Travelers who have downloaded the West Virginia Mobile ID app to their smart phone can use that for identity verification during the screening process in lieu of handing over a physical photo ID and boarding pass to the TSA security officer at the entry to the checkpoints at West Virginia International Yeager Airport and Huntington Tri-State Airport and other airports nationwide.
